Security officers in Lamu are pursuing wounded al Shabaab militants who fled during an operation in which 10 militants were killed in Boni Forest on Monday. Kenya Defence Forces have alerted health facilities in Lamu, Tana River, Garissa and the entire Coast region to be on the lookout for patients with gunshot wounds. KDF had attackedan al Shabaab camp in Taksile deep inside the forest. The soldiers reported that an unknown number of fighters suffered gunshot wounds and fled. AK-47 rifles and ammunition were recovered. Three KDF soldiers were wounded.